Requirements
------------
carnarvon needs the following dependencies:

    * cvs
    * subversion
    * python-2.x-MySQLdb
    * mysql-server
    * gnuplot
    * apache
    * mod_php
    * php5

Install
-------
You can install cvsanaly running setup.py script:

    # python setup.py install

If you don't have root privileges, add to your $PATH the directory which contains cvsanaly.

    $ export PATH=$PATH:$HOME/cvsanaly/

You are ready to use cvsanaly!

Running cvsanaly
---------------
Run cvsanaly in your local repository checkout and run cvsanaly:

    $ cd project/
    ~/project$ cvsanaly <username> <password> <database> <hostname>

Credits
-------

CVSAnalY has been developed at the Universidad Rey Juan Carlos in Móstoles, near Madrid (Spain). It is part of 
a wider research on Libre Software Engineering, a project that aims to gain knowledge on the process 
that happens when Libre Software is generated.

If you want, you can get more information on the project in http://cvsanaly.tigris.org or http://libresoft.urjc.es


